        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\n\t\t\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t  \n          \n        \n      \n    \n\n    Thu Oct 15, 2026 • 7:30pm\n\n  \n          Comedy\n    \n          Drag\n      \n\n  Event length: 140 minutes\n\n      Admission $61.50 | Admission $52.25\n    \n      Ticket prices include all taxes and fees.\n    \n  \n\n\n      \n  \n    Buy tickets\n  \n\n  \n  \n  \n  \n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t  \n    \n      \n                  God Is A Scottish Drag Queen Halloween Spooktacular\n        \n                  \n            Price Area 1 $61.50 | Price Area 2 $52.25 //The beloved deity in a floral power suit returns with a spook-tacular twist! God descends from the heavens (or perhaps a haunted attic?) to hilariously roast everything from pumpkin spice lattes to demonic possession in a laugh-out-loud night of comedy. Expect divine commentary on the bizarre traditions of Halloween, terrifying costume choices, and the true horror of candy corn. A seasonal special packed with sass, satire, and supernatural wit—because nothing is scarier than eternal damnation…except maybe Spirit Halloween.\nCreated by comedian Mike Delamont and developed into a two-act show with co-director/co-writer Chantelle Delamont, the original production premiered in 2015 at Winnipeg's Pantages Theatre. Mike Delamont is a critically acclaimed performer and three-time Canadian Comedy Award-nominated from Victoria, BC. He has appeared on radio with CBC's Laugh Out Loud, CBC's The Debaters, and SiriusXM's Top Comic. Halifax Comedy Festival, Winnipeg Comedy Festival, and at the World Famous Comedy Store in Los Angeles.\nPresented by Quatro Entertainment\n          \n        \n              \n\n      \n  \n    Event Info\n\n          \n        Category: Comedy      \n    \n          \n        Genre: Drag      \n    \n          \n        Event Length: 140 minutes\n      \n    \n      \n  \n  \t\t\n\n\n      \n    