        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t  \n          \n        \n      \n    \n\n    Fri Oct 16, 2026 • 7:30pm\n\n  \n          Music\n    \n          Trad\n      \n\n  Event length: 150 minutes\n\n      Admission $120.00 | Admission $97.00 | Admission $85.50\n    \n      Ticket prices include all taxes and fees.\n    \n  \n\n\n      \n  \n    Buy tickets\n  \n\n  \n  \n  \n  \n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t  \n    \n      \n                  Loreena McKennitt: The Mask and Mirror\n        \n                  \n            A Seating $120.00 | B Seating $97.00 | C Seating $85.50 // Canadian singer-songwriter, Loreena McKennitt, will be commemorating the 30th anniversary of her album, The Mask and The Mirror, which weaves together Celtic, Spanish and Moroccan influences. Loreena will be accompanied by Caroline Lavelle on cello, Brian Hughes on guitar, Hugh Marsh on violin, Dudley Phillips on bass and Robert Brian on drums. The first set will feature fan favourites, while the second will include every song on the album. McKennitt’s music has sold more than 14 million albums worldwide.\n          \n        \n              \n\n      \n  \n    Event Info\n\n          \n        Category: Music      \n    \n          \n        Genre: Trad      \n    \n          \n        Event Length: 150 minutes\n      \n    \n      \n  \n  \t\t\n\n\n      \n      Venue\n\n              Imperial Theatre\n      \n              12 King Square South, Saint John NB, E2L 5B8\n      \n              \n          \n            View on Google Maps\n          \n        \n          \n  \n  \n\n\n\n{\n    \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\n    \"@type\": \"Event\",\n    \"@id\": \"https://imperialtheatre.ca/event/loreena-mckennitt-the-mask-and-mirror/20201AVQHKKMVCNSSQSPNTVCQPQCKBBPV/#event-20201avqhkkmvcnssqspntvcqpqckbbpv\",\n    \"name\": \"Loreena McKennitt: The Mask and Mirror\",\n    \"url\": \"https://imperialtheatre.ca/event/loreena-mckennitt-the-mask-and-mirror/20201AVQHKKMVCNSSQSPNTVCQPQCKBBPV/\",\n    \"eventAttendanceMode\": \"https://schema.org/OfflineEventAttendanceMode\",\n    \"eventStatus\": \"https://schema.org/EventScheduled\",\n    \"location\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Place\",\n        \"name\": \"Imperial Theatre\",\n        \"sameAs\": [\n            \"http://kg.artsdata.ca/resource/K11-193\",\n            \"http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q3527482\"\n        ],\n        \"address\": {\n            \"@type\": \"PostalAddress\",\n            \"streetAddress\": \"12 King Square South\",\n            \"addressLocality\": \"Saint John\",\n            \"postalCode\": \"E2L 5B8\",\n            \"addressRegion\": \"New Brunswick\",\n            \"addressCountry\": {\n                \"@type\": \"Country\",\n                \"name\": \"CA\"\n            }\n        }\n    },\n    \"organizer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Organization\",\n        \"name\": \"Imperial Theatre\",\n        \"url\": \"https://imperialtheatre.ca/\"\n    },\n    \"description\": \"A Seating $120.00 | B Seating $97.00 | C Seating $85.50 // Canadian singer-songwriter, Loreena McKennitt, will be commemorating the 30th anniversary of her album, The Mask and The Mirror, which weaves together Celtic, Spanish and Moroccan influences. Loreena will be accompanied by Caroline Lavelle on cello, Brian Hughes on guitar, Hugh Marsh on violin, Dudley Phillips on bass and Robert Brian on drums. The first set will feature fan favourites, while the second will include every song on the album. McKennitt’s music has sold more than 14 million albums worldwide.\",\n    \"image\": [\n        \"https://system.spektrix.com/imperialtheatrenewbrunswick/files/772452ff-0486-4a61-8d62-d32d5395fcba.jpg\"\n    ],\n    \"startDate\": \"2026-10-16T16:30:00-03:00\",\n    \"offers\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Offer\",\n        \"url\": \"https://imperialtheatrenewbrunswick.spektrix.com/imperialtheatrenewbrunswick/website/EventDetails.aspx?EventId=2020