        "@id": "https://imperialtheatre.ca/event/e-t-e-amants-volages/36201ASKGPVLCNJNCMBLVSLJHKQPCHTRV/"
      }
    ],
    "https://schema.org/mainContentOfPage": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\n\t\t\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t  \n          \n        \n      \n    \n\n    Thu Oct 22, 2026 • 7:30pm\n\n  \n          Music\n    \n          Folk / Alt\n      \n\n  Event length: 90 minutes\n\n      Admission $35.00\n    \n      Ticket prices include all taxes and fees.\n    \n  \n\n\n      \n  \n    Buy tickets\n  \n\n      \n      IT Member Event\n    \n  \n  \n  \n  \n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t  \n    \n      \n                  É.T.É: Amants Volages\n        \n                  \n            Regular $35 || Member $30 ||\n\"The fruitful meeting of three young musicians with vibrant artistic journeys, É.T.É propose a dynamic\nand contemporary vision of Québécois trad music. With influences from jazz, progressive rock, and\nclassical music, violinist Élisabeth Moquin, bouzouki player Thierry Clouette and cellist Élisabeth\nGiroux create their own trad universe with original compositions and unique arrangements of\nQuébécois and Acadian repertoire. Their rich vocal harmonies, their groove, their ease at their\ninstruments and their electrifying simpatico onstage transforms the ordinary kitchen party into an\nunforgettable show! Following the release of their first album Le boire des minuits in 2017, É.T.É won\nthe “Emerging” prize from Grands prix Desjardins de la culture de Lanaudière in 2017; “Discovery of\nthe Year” from OPUS 2017-2018; the “People’s Choice” prize from Cabaret festif in 2018; the Linda\nLemay award from Festival international de la chanson de Granby 2019; and a “Lucien” from GAMIQ\n(Québec Independent Music Awards) in 2020. Their second album, Les quatre roses, was nominated\nat both OPUS and ADISQ in 2020. The group has toured extensively throughout Canada, the USA,\nScotland, Belgium and Australia. Their most recent album, Sur ces eaux, was released in November\n2022.\"\n          \n        \n              \n\n      \n  \n    Event Info\n\n          \n        Category: Music      \n    \n          \n        Genre: Folk / Alt      \n    \n          \n        Event Length: 90 minutes\n      \n    \n      \n  \n  \t\t\n\n\n      \n      Venue\n\n              Imperial Theatre\n      \n              12 King Square South, Saint John NB, E2L 5B8\n      \n              \n          \n            View on Google Maps\n          \n        \n          \n  \n  \n\n\n\n{\n    \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\n    \"@type\": \"Event\",\n    \"@id\": \"https://imperialtheatre.ca/event/e-t-e-amants-volages/36201ASKGPVLCNJNCMBLVSLJHKQPCHTRV/#event-36201askgpvlcnjncmblvsljhkqpchtrv\",\n    \"name\": \"É.T.É: Amants Volages\",\n    \"url\": \"https://imperialtheatre.ca/event/e-t-e-amants-volages/36201ASKGPVLCNJNCMBLVSLJHKQPCHTRV/\",\n    \"eventAttendanceMode\": \"https://schema.org/OfflineEventAttendanceMode\",\n    \"eventStatus\": \"https://schema.org/EventScheduled\",\n    \"location\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Place\",\n        \"name\": \"Imperial Theatre\",\n        \"sameAs\": [\n            \"http://kg.artsdata.ca/resource/K11-193\",\n            \"http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q3527482\"\n        ],\n        \"address\": {\n            \"@type\": \"PostalAddress\",\n            \"streetAddress\": \"12 King Square South\",\n            \"addressLocality\": \"Saint John\",\n            \"postalCode\": \"E2L 5B8\",\n            \"addressRegion\": \"New Brunswick\",\n            \"addressCountry\": {\n                \"@type\": \"Country\",\n                \"name\": \"CA\"\n            }\n        }\n    },\n    \"organizer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Organization\",\n        \"name\": \"Imperial Theatre\",\n        \"url\": \"https://imperialtheatre.ca/\"\n    },\n    \"description\": \"Regular $35 || Member $30 || \\\"The fruitful meeting of three young musicians with vibrant artistic journeys, É.T.É propose a dynamic and contemporary vision of Québécois trad music. With influences from jazz, progressive rock, and classical music, violinist Élisabeth Moquin, bouzouki player Thierry Clouette and cellist Élisabeth Giroux create their own trad universe with original compositions and unique arrangements of Québécois and Acadian repertoire. Their rich vocal harmonies, their groove, their ease at their instruments and their electrifying simpatico onstage transforms the ordinary kitchen party into an unforgettable show! Following the release of their first album Le boire des minuits in 2017, É.T.É won the “Emerging” prize from Grands prix Desjardins de la culture de Lanaudière in 2017; “Discovery of the Year” from OPUS 2017-2018; the “People’s Choice” prize from Cabaret festif in 2018; the Linda Lemay award from Festival international de la chanson de Granby 2019; and a “Lucien” from GAMIQ (Québec Independent Music Awards) in 2020. Their second album, Les quatre roses, was nominated at both OPUS and ADISQ in 2020. The group has toured extensively throughout Canada, the USA, Scotland, Belgium and Australia. Their most recent album, Sur ces eaux, was released in November 2022.\\\"\",\n    \"image\": [\n        \"https://system.spektrix.com/imperialtheatrenewbrunswick/files/d9d20d26-ce03-4ff0-962b-866d1643e639.jpg\"\n    ],\n    \"startDate\": \"2026-10-22T16:30:00-03:00\",\n    \"offers\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Offer\",\n        \"url\": \"https://imperialtheatrenewbrunswick.spektrix.com/imperialtheatrenewbrunswick/website/EventDetails.aspx?EventId=36201ASKGPVLCNJNCMBLVSLJHKQPCHTRV\",\n        \"availability\": \"https://schema.org/InStock\",\n        \"validFrom\": \"2026-10-22T16:30:00-03:00\"\n    },\n    \"performer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Thing\",\n        \"additionalType\": [\n            \"http://dbpedia.org/ontology/Agent\",\n            \"http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/Agent\"\n        ],\n        \"name\": \"É.T.É: Amants Volages\"\n    }\n}\n\n\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\n\t\t\n\t\n\n\n\n\t"
      }
