        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\n\t\t\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t  \n          \n        \n      \n    \n\n    Sat Oct 24, 2026 • 8:00pm\n\n  \n          Music\n    \n          Tribute\n      \n\n  Event length: 105 minutes\n\n      Admission $66.25\n    \n      Ticket prices include all taxes and fees.\n    \n  \n\n\n      \n  \n    Buy tickets\n  \n\n  \n  \n  \n  \n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t  \n    \n      \n                  Classic Albums Live: Supertramp - Breakfast In America\n        \n                  \n            Admission $66.25 // Supertramp took over where the Beatles left off.  With fantastic arrangements, soaring vocals and deft musicianship - Supertramp found their way into your heart. “Goodbye Stranger” is a song I sang to my sons when they were little. “The Logical Song” makes you believe in hope. Back in the day, I worked in the record department of a department store. I’d blast Breakfast in\nAmerica and, as though in a trance, people would buy the album.  It’s an album that accompanies us through life.\nThe two distinct vocals within Supertramp are, like the Beatles, the secret ingredient. \nWhen rehearsing the album, we spent a lot of time getting all the layered vocals, they’re complex, melodic and full of meaning and the sound becomes a siren of joy.\nSupertramp ruled the 80s with Breakfast in America.  The album was everywhere. Hit after hit. \nFunny - the one song that wasn’t released as a single is my personal favourite track - “Child of Vision”. It’s a deep, up tempo, hypnotic song that sends the listener on a trip.  We’ll be performing that song and the rest of the album in a way that no one else in world does; note for note - cut for cut.\nCraig Martin | Founder, Classic Albums Live\n          \n        \n              \n\n      \n  \n    Event Info\n\n          \n        Category: Music      \n    \n          \n        Genre: Tribute      \n    \n          \n        Event Length: 105 minutes\n      \n    \n      \n  \n  \t\t\n\n\n      \n      Venue\n\n              Imperial Theatre\n      \n              12 King Square South, Saint John NB, E2L 5B8\n      \n              \n          \n            View on Google Maps\n          \n        \n          \n  \n  \n\n\n\n{\n    \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\n    \"@type\": \"Event\",\n    \"@id\": \"https://imperialtheatre.ca/event/classic-albums-live-supertramp-breakfast-in-america/29601AVVVGLGMQTHTLNRNLGJBCQJTVHSN/#event-29601avvvglgmqthtlnrnlgjbcqjtvhsn\",\n    \"name\": \"Classic Albums Live: Supertramp - Breakfast In America\",\n    \"url\": \"https://imperialtheatre.ca/event/classic-albums-live-supertramp-breakfast-in-america/29601AVVVGLGMQTHTLNRNLGJBCQJTVHSN/\",\n    \"eventAttendanceMode\": \"https://schema.org/OfflineEventAttendanceMode\",\n    \"eventStatus\": \"https://schema.org/EventScheduled\",\n    \"location\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Place\",\n        \"name\": \"Imperial Theatre\",\n        \"sameAs\": [\n            \"http://kg.artsdata.ca/resource/K11-193\",\n            \"http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q3527482\"\n        ],\n        \"address\": {\n            \"@type\": \"PostalAddress\",\n            \"streetAddress\": \"12 King Square South\",\n            \"addressLocality\": \"Saint John\",\n            \"postalCode\": \"E2L 5B8\",\n            \"addressRegion\": \"New Brunswick\",\n            \"addressCountry\": {\n                \"@type\": \"Country\",\n                \"name\": \"CA\"\n            }\n        }\n    },\n    \"organizer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Organization\",\n        \"name\": \"Imperial Theatre\",\n        \"url\": \"https://imperialtheatre.ca/\"\n    },\n    \"description\": \"Admission $66.25 // Supertramp took over where the Beatles left off.  With fantastic arrangements, soaring vocals and deft musicianship - Supertramp found their way into your heart. “Goodbye Stranger” is a song I sang to my sons when they were little. “The Logical Song” makes you believe in hope. Back in the day, I worked in the record department of a department store. I’d blast Breakfast in America and, as though in a trance, people would buy the album.  It’s an album that accompanies us through life. The two distinct vocals within Supertramp are, like the Beatles, the secret ingredient.  When rehearsing the album, we spent a lot of time getting all the layered vocals, they’re complex, melodic and full of meaning and the sound becomes a siren of joy. Supertramp ruled the 80s with Breakfast in America.  The album was everywhere. Hit after hit.  Funny - the one song that wasn’t released as a single is my personal favourite track - “Child of Vision”. It’s a deep, up tempo, hypnotic song that sends the listener on a trip.  We’ll be performing that song and the rest of the album in a way that no one else in world does; note for note - cut for cut. Craig Martin | Founder, Classic Albums Live\",\n    \"image\": [\n        \"https://system.spektrix.com/imperialtheatrenewbrunswick/files/127b0276-7818-46fb-b717-a4398e2d603d.jpg\"\n    ],\n    \"startDate\": \"2026-10-24T17:00:00-03:00\",\n    \"offers\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Offer\",\n        \"url\": \"https://imperialtheatrenewbrunswick.spektrix.com/imperialtheatrenewbrunswick/website/EventDetails.aspx?EventId=29601AVVVGLGMQTHTLNRNLGJBCQJTVHSN\",\n        \"availability\": \"https://schema.org/InStock\",\n        \"validFrom\": \"2026-10-24T17:00:00-03:00\"\n    },\n    \"performer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Thing\",\n        \"additionalType\": [\n            \"http://dbpedia.org/ontology/Agent\",\n            \"http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/Agent\"\n        ],\n        \"name\": \"Classic Albums Live: Supertramp - Breakfast In America\"\n    }\n}\n\n\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\n\t\n\t\n\n\n\n\t\t\n\t\n\n\n\n\t"
      }
