        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t  \n          \n        \n      \n    \n\n    Fri Nov 13, 2026 • 7:30pm\n\n  \n          Music\n    \n          Country\n      \n\n  Event length: 75 minutes\n\n      Admission $65.00 | Admission $55.00\n    \n      Ticket prices include all taxes and fees.\n    \n  \n\n\n      \n  \n    Buy tickets\n  \n\n      \n      IT Member Event\n    \n  \n  \n  \n  \n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t  \n    \n      \n                  A Coast to Coast Cowboy Christmas\n        \n                  \n            $65 A Regular || $60 A Member // $55 B Regular || $50 B Member // Canadian country legends George Canyon and Aaron Pritchett are back again with their coast-to-coast Cowboy Christmas tour—celebrating the season with classic hits and holiday favourites. \nWith over 25 years of chart-topping music and multiple CCMA wins between them, these two powerhouse performers bring their signature styles, unmatched energy, and heartfelt storytelling to the stage for a festive night of country magic.\nGeorge Canyon, a Nova Scotia native and Platinum-selling artist, has earned Juno, CCMA, and ECMA Awards, and was inducted into the NS Country Music Hall of Fame. Known for hits like \"Just Like You\", \"I Got This\", and \"I Want You to Live\", George is also a respected humanitarian, national anthem singer for the Calgary Flames, and the author of his 2022 memoir My Country.\nAaron Pritchett is known for his electrifying live shows and 13 Top Ten hits, including \"Hold My Beer\", \"Better When I Do\", and \"Warm Safe Place\". With decades of fan devotion, a CCMA SOCAN Songwriter of the Year Award, and his own charitable golf tournament, Aaron continues to evolve while staying true to his country roots.\nDon’t miss this unforgettable holiday concert from two of Canada’s finest.\n          \n        \n              \n\n      \n  \n    Event Info\n\n          \n        Category: Music      \n    \n          \n        Genre: Country      \n    \n          \n        Event Length: 75 minutes\n      \n    \n      \n  \n  \t\t\n\n\n      \n      Venue\n\n              Imperial Theatre\n      \n              12 King Square South, Saint John NB, E2L 5B8\n      \n              \n          \n            View on Google Maps\n          \n        \n          \n  \n  \n\n\n\n{\n    \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\n    \"@type\": \"Event\",\n    \"@id\": \"https://imperialtheatre.ca/event/a-coast-to-coast-cowboy-christmas/37201ANNHRQCTNHTBVHBGGJGJCBQDGBJG/#event-37201annhrqctnhtbvhbggjgjcbqdgbjg\",\n    \"name\": \"A Coast to Coast Cowboy Christmas\",\n    \"url\": \"https://imperialtheatre.ca/event/a-coast-to-coast-cowboy-christmas/37201ANNHRQCTNHTBVHBGGJGJCBQDGBJG/\",\n    \"eventAttendanceMode\": \"https://schema.org/OfflineEventAttendanceMode\",\n    \"eventStatus\": \"https://schema.org/EventScheduled\",\n    \"location\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Place\",\n        \"name\": \"Imperial Theatre\",\n        \"sameAs\": [\n            \"http://kg.artsdata.ca/resource/K11-193\",\n            \"http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q3527482\"\n        ],\n        \"address\": {\n            \"@type\": \"PostalAddress\",\n            \"streetAddress\": \"12 King Square South\",\n            \"addressLocality\": \"Saint John\",\n            \"postalCode\": \"E2L 5B8\",\n            \"addressRegion\": \"New Brunswick\",\n            \"addressCountry\": {\n                \"@type\": \"Country\",\n                \"name\": \"CA\"\n            }\n        }\n    },\n    \"organizer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Organization\",\n        \"name\": \"Imperial Theatre\",\n        \"url\": \"https://imperialtheatre.ca/\"\n    },\n    \"description\": \"$65 A Regular || $60 A Member // $55 B Regular || $50 B Member // Canadian country legends George Canyon and Aaron Pritchett are back again with their coast-to-coast Cowboy Christmas tour—celebrating the season with classic hits and holiday favourites. With over 25 years of chart-topping music and multiple CCMA wins between them, these two powerhouse performers bring their signature styles, unmatched energy, and heartfelt storytelling to the stage for a festive night of country magic. George Canyon, a Nova Scotia native and Platinum-selling artist, has earned Juno, CCMA, and ECMA Awards, and was inducted into the NS Country Music Hall of Fame. Known for hits like \\\"Just Like You\\\", \\\"I Got This\\\", and \\\"I Want You to Live\\\", George is also a respected humanitarian, national anthem singer for the Calgary Flames, and the author of his 2022 memoir My Country. Aaron Pritchett is known for his electrifying live shows and 13 Top Ten hits, including \\\"Hold My Beer\\\", \\\"Better When I Do\\\", and \\\"Warm Safe Place\\\". With decades of fan devotion, a CCMA SOCAN Songwriter of the Year Award, and his own charitable golf tournament, Aaron continues to evolve while staying true to his country roots. Don’t miss this unforgettable holiday concert from two of Canada’s finest.\",\n    \"image\": [\n        \"https://system.spektrix.com/imperialtheatrenewbrunswick/files/95f6dde8-84a6-4cd4-a650-62c80d976352.jpg\"\n    ],\n    \"startDate\": \"2026-11-13T15:30:00-04:00\",\n    \"offers\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Offer\",\n        \"url\": \"https://imperialtheatrenewbrunswick.spektrix.com/imperialtheatrenewbrunswick/website/EventDetails.aspx?EventId=37201ANNHRQCTNHTBVHBGGJGJCBQDGBJG\",\n        \"availability\": \"https://schema.org/InStock\",\n        \"validFrom\": \"2026-11-13T15:30:00-04:00\"\n    },\n    \"performer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Thing\",\n        \"additionalType\": [\n            \"http://dbpedia.org/ontology/Agent\",\n            \"http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/Agent\"\n        ],\n        \"name\": \"A Coast to Coast Cowboy Christmas\"\n    }\n}\n\n\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\n\t"
