    "https://schema.org/text": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t  \n          \n        \n      \n    \n\n    Sat Jan 16, 2027 • 7:30pm\n\n  \n          Theatre\n    \n          Presentation\n      \n\n  Event length: 90 minutes\n\n      Admission $45.00\n    \n      Ticket prices include all taxes and fees.\n    \n  \n\n\n      \n  \n    Buy tickets\n  \n\n      \n      IT Member Event\n    \n  \n  \n  \n  \n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\n\t  \n    \n      \n                  Zuppa: The Final Recordings of an Almost Extinct Bird\n        \n                  \n            $45 Regular || $40 Member || \nMature Content || Recommended 14+ (Sexual innuendo, strong language, themes of death and dying)\nA very personal story about the beginnings and endings of love, life, humanity and the cosmos, and an invitation to consider one's relationship with deep time, no matter what rocks you may find yourself on. Fred has a lot on his mind. The origins of the universe, for starters. The fabric of spacetime, too. The formation of the Earth, plate tectonics, the fossil record, gravitational waves, dark matter, winding valley roads, campfires, pottery cafes—the list goes on and on. There’s also the matter of the giant salty egg, the man in the comfy blue chair, and the burning question: “Is this good? What I’m doing? With mine? My time?”\nThis ecstatic, bittersweet, solo performance juxtaposes a queer love story with the scope of the cosmos and geology of Nova Scotia. Driven by Stewart Legere’s captivating performance, accompanied by seamless video and sound design, the show runs 90 minutes and contains mature content and strong language.  Developed in association with The Fundy Geological Museum, \"\"Final Recordings...\"\" had its premiere run at Eastern Front Theatre's 2025 Stages Festival. Performed, composed and sound designed by Stewart Legere, with projections by Christian Ludwig Hansen, lighting by Jessica Lewis, costumes, set and props by Leesa Hamilton, and directed by Ben Stone, “Final Recordings...” is where TED Talk, sob story, and cottagecore collide.    CREDITS\nBen Stone - director\nStewart Legere - performer\nBen Stone and Stewart Legere - playwrights\nFundy Geological Museum, Regan Maloney - science consultant\nStewart Legere - composer\nChristian Ludwig Hansen - projection design\nStewart Legere - sound design\nJess Lewis - lighting design\nLeesa Hamilton - costume, prop and set design\nBernie Francis - Mi'kmaw language consultant\nSophie Schade - producer\nMary Fay Coady - interim producer\nGaby Milner - FSPA student apprentice\n          \n        \n              \n\n      \n  \n    Event Info\n\n          \n        Category: Theatre      \n    \n          \n        Genre: Presentation      \n    \n          \n        Event Length: 90 minutes\n      \n    \n      \n  \n  \t\t\n\n\n      \n      Venue\n\n              Imperial Theatre\n      \n              12 King Square South, Saint John NB, E2L 5B8\n      \n              \n          \n            View on Google Maps\n          \n        \n          \n  \n  \n\n\n\n{\n    \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\n    \"@type\": \"Event\",\n    \"@id\": \"https://imperialtheatre.ca/event/zuppa-the-final-recordings-of-an-almost-extinct-bird/38801AQDNRKLTDJNRGTHNNSDTQVMLRTCD/#event-38801aqdnrkltdjnrgthnnsdtqvmlrtcd\",\n    \"name\": \"Zuppa: The Final Recordings of an Almost Extinct Bird\",\n    \"url\": \"https://imperialtheatre.ca/event/zuppa-the-final-recordings-of-an-almost-extinct-bird/38801AQDNRKLTDJNRGTHNNSDTQVMLRTCD/\",\n    \"eventAttendanceMode\": \"https://schema.org/OfflineEventAttendanceMode\",\n    \"eventStatus\": \"https://schema.org/EventScheduled\",\n    \"location\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Place\",\n        \"name\": \"Imperial Theatre\",\n        \"sameAs\": [\n            \"http://kg.artsdata.ca/resource/K11-193\",\n            \"http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q3527482\"\n        ],\n        \"address\": {\n            \"@type\": \"PostalAddress\",\n            \"streetAddress\": \"12 King Square South\",\n            \"addressLocality\": \"Saint John\",\n            \"postalCode\": \"E2L 5B8\",\n            \"addressRegion\": \"New Brunswick\",\n            \"addressCountry\": {\n                \"@type\": \"Country\",\n                \"name\": \"CA\"\n            }\n        }\n    },\n    \"organizer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Organization\",\n        \"name\": \"Imperial Theatre\",\n        \"url\": \"https://imperialtheatre.ca/\"\n    },\n    \"description\": \"$45 Regular || $40 Member || Mature Content || Recommended 14+ (Sexual innuendo, strong language, themes of death and dying) A very personal story about the beginnings and endings of love, life, humanity and the cosmos, and an invitation to consider one's relationship with deep time, no matter what rocks you may find yourself on. Fred has a lot on his mind. The origins of the universe, for starters. The fabric of spacetime, too. The formation of the Earth, plate tectonics, the fossil record, gravitational waves, dark matter, winding valley roads, campfires, pottery cafes—the list goes on and on. There’s also the matter of the giant salty egg, the man in the comfy blue chair, and the burning question: “Is this good? What I’m doing? With mine? My time?” This ecstatic, bittersweet, solo performance juxtaposes a queer love story with the scope of the cosmos and geology of Nova Scotia. Driven by Stewart Legere’s captivating performance, accompanied by seamless video and sound design, the show runs 90 minutes and contains mature content and strong language. Developed in association with The Fundy Geological Museum, \\\"\\\"Final Recordings...\\\"\\\" had its premiere run at Eastern Front Theatre's 2025 Stages Festival. Performed, composed and sound designed by Stewart Legere, with projections by Christian Ludwig Hansen, lighting by Jessica Lewis, costumes, set and props by Leesa Hamilton, and directed by Ben Stone, “Final Recordings...” is where TED Talk, sob story, and cottagecore collide. CREDITS Ben Stone - director Stewart Legere - performer Ben Stone and Stewart Legere - playwrights Fundy Geological Museum, Regan Maloney - science consultant Stewart Legere - composer Christian Ludwig Hansen - projection design Stewart Legere - sound design Jess Lewis - lighting design Leesa Hamilton - costume, prop and set design Bernie Francis - Mi'kmaw language consultant Sophie Schade - producer Mary Fay Coady - interim producer Gaby Milner - FSPA student apprentice\",\n    \"image\": [\n        \"https://system.spektrix.com/imperialtheatrenewbrunswick/files/da1d1a13-0b82-4d3c-b956-c5e969c5ac87.jpg\"\n    ],\n    \"startDate\": \"2027-01-16T15:30:00-04:00\",\n    \"offers\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Offer\",\n        \"url\": \"https://imperialtheatrenewbrunswick.spektrix.com/imperialtheatrenewbrunswick/website/EventDetails.aspx?EventId=38801AQDNRKLTDJNRGTHNNSDTQVMLRTCD\",\n        \"availability\": \"https://schema.org/InStock\",\n        \"validFrom\": \"2027-01-16T15:30:00-04:00\"\n    },\n    \"performer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Thing\",\n        \"additionalType\": [\n            \"http://dbpedia.org/ontology/Agent\",\n            \"http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/Agent\"\n        ],\n        \"name\": \"Zuppa: The Final Recordings of an Almost Extinct Bird\"\n    }\n}\n\n\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\n\t"
