    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Hey Viola!"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "$30 Regular || $10 Member || Hey Viola! is a musical production created by Krystle Dos Santos and Tracey Power that explores the life and legacy of Canadian civil rights hero Viola Desmond. The show serves as both a history lesson and a musical revue, highlighting Desmond’s courage as a businesswoman, feminist, and civil rights pioneer who famously challenged racial segregation at Nova Scotia’s Roseland cinema in 1946. Format: The production uses inspirational music to tell Desmond’s story, featuring a diverse song list including tracks like \"\"A Change is Gonna Come\"\" and \"\"Feeling Good\"\". Lead Performer: Krystle Dos Santos. Director/Co-Creator: Tracey Power. Associate Director: Sereana Malani. Musicians: Steve Charles (MD/Guitar/Bass), Chris Davis (Drums/Trumpet), and Mary Ancheta (Piano). Designers: Drew Facey (Set), CS Fergusson-Vaux (Costume), and Jillian White (Lighting)."
      }
