stry to shine at its fullest, while the Adams’ celebrated partnership and Kutnowski’s original composition anchor the program in New Brunswick’s musical identity. The bilingual and cultural fabric of the province finds a natural resonance through Giraud’s French origins and the Adams’ deep roots in the region’s classical tradition.\",\n    \"image\": [\n        \"https://system.spektrix.com/imperialtheatrenewbrunswick/files/44716710-c68a-4e23-998e-0e2c76c881a3.jpg\"\n    ],\n    \"startDate\": \"2027-04-16T16:30:00-03:00\",\n    \"offers\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Offer\",\n        \"url\": \"https://imperialtheatrenewbrunswick.spektrix.com/imperialtheatrenewbrunswick/website/EventDetails.aspx?EventId=42602AVHSCVRKTVVDBKLHTRLBRGRJKKKD\",\n        \"availability\": \"https://schema.org/InStock\",\n        \"validFrom\": \"2027-04-16T16:30:00-03:00\"\n    },\n    \"performer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Thing\",\n        \"additionalType\": [\n            \"http://dbpedia.org/ontology/Agent\",\n            \"http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/Agent\"\n        ],\n        \"name\": \"From Paris to the Maritimes\"\n    }\n}\n\n\n\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\n\n\t"
